claims:
Claims Claims 1. A composition for forming a sealing material, comprising: a (meth)acrylic compound; an epoxy compound; a photopolymerization initiator; and a thermal curing agent, wherein the (meth)acrylic compound contains a tetrahydrofuryl (mete)acrylate, and a content of the tetrahydrofuryl (mete)acrylate is 70% by mass or greater with respect to a total mass of the (meth)acrylic compound. 2. The composition for forming a sealing material according to claim 1, wherein a content of the epoxy compound is 70 to 200 parts by mass with respect to 100 parts by mass of the (meth)acrylic compound. 3. The composition for forming a sealing material according to claim 1 or 2, wherein the epoxy compound contains a flexible epoxy compound. 4. A sealing material comprising a photocured product of the composition for forming a sealing material described in any one of claims 1 to 3. 5. A sealing material, comprising: a (meth)acrylic polymer; an epoxy compound; and a thermal curing agent, wherein the (meth)acrylic polymer contains 70% by mass or greater of constituent unit represented by Formula (1) with respect to a total mass of the (meth)acrylic polymer; 

 Chemical Formula 1 where, R represents a hydrogen atom or a methyl group. 6. The sealing material according to claim 5, wherein a content of the epoxy compound is from 70 to 200 parts by mass with respect to 100 parts by mass of the (meth)acrylic polymer. 7. The sealing material according to claim 5 or 6, wherein the epoxy compound contains a flexible epoxy compound. 8. The sealing material according to any one of claims 4 to 7, wherein the sealing material is formed in a sheet shape. 9. A thermally cured product of the sealing material according to any one of claims 4 to 8. 10. A method for manufacturing an adhesive structure having a structure in which a first cured body as the thermally cured product of the sealing material described in any one of claims 4 to 8 and a second cured body containing polyvinyl chloride adhere onto an adherend, the method comprising: 

 arranging the sealing material and a polyvinyl chloride sol containing polyvinyl chloride and a plasticizer on the adherend in a state where the sealing material is in contact with the polyvinyl chloride sol; and obtaining the adhesive structure by heating the sealing material and the polyvinyl chloride sol.
